  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then drain the <strong>tofu</strong> and cut into small bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once very hot, add the <strong>tofu</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until golden all over</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>tofu</strong> to kitchen paper and set aside, reserving the pan and oil for later</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\n<p>Deseed the <strong>red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>\n<p>Top, tail, peel and slice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways, then into batons</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>wholewheat noodles </strong>to a pot and cover them with <strong>boiled water </strong>until they're fully submerged</p>\n<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-7 min until they're tender with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>noodles</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p>\n<p><strong> </strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1468.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
